## Colors Collection [/color]

### List All Colors [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "color_id": 420,
                "color_name": "seaWeed Green", 
                "color_hashcode": "#536633",
                "num_products": 420 
            }
        ]

### Create a New Color [POST]

You may create your own color using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing the name and hashcode(hex value) of the color 
and returns a JSON object with the given information and the 
color id assigned by the database.

+ Request (application/json)

        [
            {
                "color_name": "Princess Peach Pink", 
                "color_hashcode": "#F5B6FC",
            }
        ]

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /color/14

    + Body

            {
                "color_id": 14,
                "color_name": "Princess Peach Pink", 
                "color_hashcode": "#F5B6FC",
                "num_products": 0
            }
## Type Collection [/type]

### List All Types [GET]

Lists all the types plus products associated with those types
+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "type_id": 1,
                "type_name": "Mascara", 
                "avg_price": "14.0",
                "avg_rating": 4.6,
                "num_products": 2,
                "products": [
                    {
                        "product_id": 1,
                        "brand_name": "Pure Anada",
                        "product_name": "Pure Anada Natural Mascara"
                    }, {
                        "product_id": 4,
                        "brand_name": "Generic Company",
                        "product_name": "Generic Mascara"
                    }
                    
                ]
            }
        ]

### Create a New Type [POST]

You may create your own type using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing the name of the type and returns the database 
assigned typeid and some other instantiated information.
+ Request (application/json)

        [
            {
                "type_name": "Mascara", 
            }
        ]

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /type/1

    + Body

            {
                "type_id": 1,
                "type_name": "Mascara", 
                "avg_price": 0.0,
                "avg_rating": 0.0,
                "num_products": 0,
            }
